The old man says, "Hello there stranger. I'm just a regular old traveller. My name is ... uh ... Grimnir. Yeah, 
that's the ticket ... Grimnir.  I'm not in disguise at all. Say, do you happen to know the way to Mimir's well? 
No? That's okay. Carry on, then. Nothing to see here."  Then he mumbles, "I'm sure it doesn't matter. There's no
way you can guess who I am at all."

